The Australian Department of Immigration and Border Protection (DIBP) is a department of the Government of Australia that is responsible for immigration, citizenship and border control (including visa issuance).
The head of the department is the Secretary of the Department of Immigration and Border Protection, currently Michael Pezzullo, who reports to the Minister for Immigration and Border Protection, currently the Hon. Peter Dutton  and the Assistant Minister for Immigration and Border Protection, currently MP the Hon. Alex Hawke.
